<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Preparing Your Home for Sale</title>
	<style>
		body {
	font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
		margin: 20px;
		}
		
		.step {
		margin-bottom: 20px;
		padding: 20px;
		border: 1px solid #ddd;
		border-radius: 10px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
		}
		
		.step-number {
		font-weight: bold;
		font-size: 18px;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
		}
		
		.step-description {
		font-size: 16px;
		color: #666;
		}
		
		.step-icon {
		font-size: 24px;
		color: #337ab7;
		margin-right: 10px;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>

	<h1>Preparing Your Home for Sale: 8 Essential Steps</h1>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">1. Identify repairs and make a plan</div>
		<div class="step-description">Make a list of necessary repairs and prioritize them based on importance and cost. Create a budget and timeline to complete the work.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">2. Declutter and clean—make it feel spacious</div>
		<div class="step-description">Remove clutter, tidy up living areas, and give your home a deep clean to make it feel more spacious and inviting.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">3. Depersonalize your home</div>
		<div class="step-description">Remove personal items, such as family photos and decorative items, to help potential buyers imagine themselves living in the space.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">4. Paint where it needs it most</div>
		<div class="step-description">Touch up paint in high-traffic areas and rooms that need a fresh coat to make your home look well-maintained and modern.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">5. Set the stage—make it feel like home</div>
		<div class="step-description">Arrange furniture and decor to create a welcoming atmosphere and help buyers envision themselves living in the space.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">6. Keep it clean and consistent</div>
		<div class="step-description">Maintain a clean and tidy home throughout the selling process to make a good impression on potential buyers.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">7. Takeaways</div>
		<div class="step-description">Remove any unnecessary items, such as trash or excess furniture, to make your home feel more spacious and inviting.</div>
	</div>
	
	<div class="step">
		<span class="step-icon">&#x2714;</span>
		<div class="step-number">8. Home showings checklist</div>
		<div class="step-description">Create a checklist to ensure your home is ready for showings, including tasks like turning on lights, opening curtains, and tidying up.</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>